- We'd better not cause trouble. - It looks old.

1405
00:46:41,170 --> 00:46:42,270
- Nice. - Is there enough space?

1406
00:46:44,040 --> 00:46:45,109
- Yes. - Gosh.

1407
00:46:45,110 --> 00:46:46,870
- Will the owner remember him? - Is she inside?

1408
00:46:47,410 --> 00:46:48,710
- Is it the same owner? - Is it the same owner?

1409
00:46:49,710 --> 00:46:51,409
- Hi. - Hi.

1410
00:46:51,410 --> 00:46:52,910
- Hi. - It's her.

1411
00:46:54,050 --> 00:46:55,279
The owner hasn't changed.

1412
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:57,319
- Is that so? - I just got goosebumps.

1413
00:46:57,320 --> 00:46:58,819
- Really? - It's the owner from back then.

1414
00:46:58,820 --> 00:46:59,889
- Hi. - Hi.

1415
00:46:59,890 --> 00:47:01,019
Do you remember me?

1416
00:47:01,020 --> 00:47:02,960
- Of course. - You do?

1417
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:05,060
- Hi. - The owner hasn't changed.

1418
00:47:05,530 --> 00:47:07,929
Dong Hyun kept saying how good it was, so we came.

1419
00:47:07,930 --> 00:47:08,930
(The owner still remembers Dong Hyun.)

1420
00:47:08,930 --> 00:47:09,930
I was worried...

1421
00:47:09,930 --> 00:47:10,930
- the owner had changed. - Let's sit here.

1422
00:47:12,100 --> 00:47:14,600
I didn't know you still ran this restaurant.

1423
00:47:15,770 --> 00:47:16,839
What brought you all the way here?

1424
00:47:16,840 --> 00:47:18,540
- Dong Hyun... - I...

1425
00:47:18,970 --> 00:47:21,080
We were around the area and had to come.

1426
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:22,510
It reminded me of the old days.

1427
00:47:22,910 --> 00:47:24,879
Dong Hyun said he always had a meal here...

1428
00:47:24,880 --> 00:47:26,850
- after working out. - It's true.

1429
00:47:27,980 --> 00:47:29,049
In the past.

1430
00:47:29,050 --> 00:47:32,250
- We'll get two jumbo jjajangmyeon. - Okay.

1431
00:47:32,750 --> 00:47:34,360
- Two jjamppong. - Okay.

1432
00:47:34,520 --> 00:47:36,459
- One tangsuyuk. - Okay.

1433
00:47:36,460 --> 00:47:37,689
How about one yangjangpi?

1434
00:47:37,690 --> 00:47:39,890
- Sure, and one yangjangpi. - Okay.

1435
00:47:40,930 --> 00:47:42,160
My mouth is watering.

1436
00:47:42,830 --> 00:47:44,469
But the fact that this place is still here...

1437
00:47:44,470 --> 00:47:46,929
- Is everything the same? - Exactly the same.

1438
00:47:46,930 --> 00:47:48,570
- That must feel good. - Yes.

1439
00:47:48,770 --> 00:47:50,469
The fighters would come by...

1440
00:47:50,470 --> 00:47:52,440
- and eat when they won. - Really?

1441
00:47:52,970 --> 00:47:54,210
What did you eat after you won a fight, Sung Hoon?

1442
00:47:54,480 --> 00:47:57,309
I always had meat when I won.

1443
00:47:57,310 --> 00:47:59,150
- What about when you lost? - When I lost...

1444
00:47:59,410 --> 00:48:00,679
Well, when you lose,

1445
00:48:00,680 --> 00:48:02,519
even the most delicious food tastes bad.

1446
00:48:02,520 --> 00:48:04,289
- Your mind goes blank. - Exactly.

1447
00:48:04,290 --> 00:48:05,889
- Losing is... - Right.

1448
00:48:05,890 --> 00:48:07,560
I don't even want to imagine it.

1449
00:48:08,820 --> 00:48:11,060
I'm hungry. We lost the game, but...

1450
00:48:11,560 --> 00:48:12,730
Right.

1451
00:48:12,930 --> 00:48:14,730
Yet here we are, still waiting for food.

1452
00:48:15,830 --> 00:48:17,829
- Let's eat delicious food... - Yes.

1453
00:48:17,830 --> 00:48:19,600
- And cheer up. - and cheer up.

1454
00:48:20,430 --> 00:48:22,400
I haven't eaten in so long.

1455
00:48:23,270 --> 00:48:24,270
- Really? - Yes.

1456
00:48:24,271 --> 00:48:26,169
- Have you been starving yourself? - I do this thing...

1457
00:48:26,170 --> 00:48:27,939
- like a detox. - Detox.

1458
00:48:27,940 --> 00:48:30,479
- I don't eat for 36 hours. - Right.

1459
00:48:30,480 --> 00:48:32,009
How long has it been since your last meal?

1460
00:48:32,010 --> 00:48:33,379
The time is...

1461
00:48:33,380 --> 00:48:34,679
It's been around 40 hours.

1462
00:48:34,680 --> 00:48:36,019
- No way. - Since you ate?

1463
00:48:36,020 --> 00:48:37,020
- Yes. - You haven't eaten anything?

1464
00:48:37,021 --> 00:48:38,490
No. This is my first meal since.

1465
00:48:38,950 --> 00:48:41,320
His last meal was dinner two days ago.

1466
00:48:41,720 --> 00:48:42,920
- He does it every now and then. - That's...

1467
00:48:43,460 --> 00:48:45,260
the state of an actual lion.

1468
00:48:46,060 --> 00:48:48,300
- You're literally a lion. - He's...

1469
00:48:48,530 --> 00:48:50,670
He's going to start hunting tangsuyuk soon.

1470
00:48:51,070 --> 00:48:52,600
- He'll start hunting. - Literally.

1471
00:48:52,770 --> 00:48:55,239
We'll barely eat any of it.

1472
00:48:55,240 --> 00:48:56,799
(You must brace yourself when eating with a lion.)

1473
00:48:56,800 --> 00:48:58,239
- Gosh. - Gosh.

1474
00:48:58,240 --> 00:48:59,339
(The first dish arrives.)

1475
00:48:59,340 --> 00:49:00,540
- That's huge. - Amazing.

1476
00:49:00,740 --> 00:49:02,540
- Thank you for the food. - Look at the steam.

1477
00:49:02,940 --> 00:49:06,249
- It's red, right? - It looks like they used ketchup.

1478
00:49:06,250 --> 00:49:07,350
They must have.

1479
00:49:07,720 --> 00:49:08,980
It's the old-school sauce.

1480
00:49:09,720 --> 00:49:11,049
(Moaning)

1481
00:49:11,050 --> 00:49:12,420
(Exclaiming)

1482
00:49:12,590 --> 00:49:13,789
So good.

1483
00:49:13,790 --> 00:49:15,189
- It's so... - It's steaming.

1484
00:49:15,190 --> 00:49:16,360
(Meeting young Dong Hyun from 20 years back)

1485
00:49:16,820 --> 00:49:17,989
It's old-school tangsuyuk.

1486
00:49:17,990 --> 00:49:19,260
- It smells like it. - Yes.

1487
00:49:20,430 --> 00:49:23,530
(Lion Choo begins hunting for tangsuyuk.)

1488
00:49:26,530 --> 00:49:29,169
I wonder how good it'll taste after 40 hours of not eating.

1489
00:49:29,170 --> 00:49:30,170
It's good.

1490
00:49:30,640 --> 00:49:31,740
It's delicious.

1491
00:49:31,770 --> 00:49:32,770
It's so good.

1492
00:49:32,940 --> 00:49:35,010
- This is a great restaurant. - It is.

1493
00:49:35,440 --> 00:49:36,710
(Moaning)

1494
00:49:36,980 --> 00:49:38,180
The chef can cook.

1495
00:49:38,480 --> 00:49:40,050
- It's good, right? - It's been almost 30 years.

1496
00:49:40,110 --> 00:49:41,179
- Great. - Not many places...

1497
00:49:41,180 --> 00:49:42,449
make the tangsuyuk sauce this way.

1498
00:49:42,450 --> 00:49:43,579
- That's true. - Really?

1499
00:49:43,580 --> 00:49:44,590
Yes.

1500
00:49:45,350 --> 00:49:47,320
- This is so good. - It's tasty.

1501
00:49:47,420 --> 00:49:48,459
(Peeking)

1502
00:49:48,460 --> 00:49:50,759
- Sung Hoon is already... - Sung Hoon!

1503
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:52,359
- What? - He has three pieces on his plate.

1504
00:49:52,360 --> 00:49:54,060
You can't put them on your plate and eat off the big dish.

1505
00:49:54,960 --> 00:49:56,400
Seriously.

1506
00:49:57,030 --> 00:49:58,499
You can't do that.

1507
00:49:58,500 --> 00:50:00,029
That's just how I eat.

1508
00:50:00,030 --> 00:50:01,170
What are you talking about?

1509
00:50:01,200 --> 00:50:02,339
That's unfair.

1510
00:50:02,340 --> 00:50:03,500
- It's how I eat. - But...

1511
00:50:03,970 --> 00:50:05,009
- Dong Hyun. - Yes?

1512
00:50:05,010 --> 00:50:06,039
I saw you grabbing from this when you had food in front of you.

1513
00:50:06,040 --> 00:50:08,979
- Yes, you're the same! - I was showing him how he did it.

1514
00:50:08,980 --> 00:50:10,879
Athletes are so...

1515
00:50:10,880 --> 00:50:11,880
(Quickly destroying the evidence)

1516
00:50:12,080 --> 00:50:14,250
(The next dish arrives.)

1517
00:50:14,620 --> 00:50:15,620
(Sweet and sour yangjangpi)

1518
00:50:15,621 --> 00:50:17,519
- That's generous. - A little bit of mustard?

1519
00:50:17,520 --> 00:50:19,550
(Adding piquancy with mustard)

1520
00:50:20,090 --> 00:50:22,089
- I think we should cut it once. - Sure.

1521
00:50:22,090 --> 00:50:23,890
I'll cut it.

1522
00:50:28,660 --> 00:50:29,730
It's delicious.

1523
00:50:30,400 --> 00:50:31,530
We finished tangsuyuk.

1524
00:50:31,830 --> 00:50:33,430
Oh, you finished it while I was doing this.

1525
00:50:34,340 --> 00:50:35,469
(Laughing)

1526
00:50:35,470 --> 00:50:36,500
Gosh.

1527
00:50:36,640 --> 00:50:38,510
- We only ate one. - I came here after 20 years,

1528
00:50:38,840 --> 00:50:40,140
and you finished it while I was mixing the other dish.

1529
00:50:40,910 --> 00:50:43,209
- You have some on your plate. - Right.

